    "ts": "2026-03-20T04:41:48+00:00",
    "headline": "FedEx sees global demand holding amid Iran war, raises profit outlook",
    "summary": "<body><p>STORY: FedEx said on Thursday that global demand is holding steady despite the war in Iran.</p><p>CEO Raj Subramaniam said that demand for the first two weeks of March has been in line with FedEx's expectations.</p><p>Executives said the Middle East accounts for a small part of the global delivery company.</p><p>According to analysts, about 8% of FedEx's international export volume flows through hubs in the war-affected region.</p><p>The company also reported strong fiscal earnings for the quarter ended February 28, helped by healthy delivery demand and cost controls during the pivotal holiday quarter.</p><p>Subramaniam said the peak season was \"the most profitable\" in FedEx history.</p><p>FedEx raised its full‑year profit forecast, sending shares up 9% in after‑hours trading.</p><p>With the war in Iran, oil prices hit over $100 a barrel.</p><p>But the shipping giant says the fuel surcharge it has in place is \"doing its job.\"&nbsp;</p><p>FedEx said its outlook assumes no additional geopolitical disruptions.</p><p>But adds that the U.S.-Israeli war on Iran could weigh on fourth-quarter performance if soaring fuel costs prompt customers to pull back.</p></body>",
    "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/video/fedex-sees-global-demand-holding-044148238.html",
    "source": "Reuters Videos",
    "provider": "yfinance",
